            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Restore NASA Science funding to $9 billion to maintain U.S. leadership and counter rapid lunar and planetary expansion by China\n* NASA Science delivers a 3-to-1 economic return, supporting a specialized industrial workforce and innovation economy\n* Consistent investment allows NASA to follow peer-reviewed Decadal Survey priorities for transformative scientific discovery\n* Reverses the instability of previous budget cycles that led to the loss of thousands of skilled aerospace jobs",
            "rationale": "Justification draws on advocacy talking points regarding international competition, economic ROI, and the importance of Decadal Surveys for scientific priority setting.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
