            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_1060492821:e719f01293cb",
            "label": "Why is this request important to New Jersey and the 12th Congressional District?",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Direct investment of $39,528,990 in NASA Science obligations within NJ-12 institutions between FY 2023 and FY 2025\n* Supports high-impact research at Princeton University, including projects for cosmic light measurement and atmospheric imaging\n* Sustains hundreds of local STEM research positions through active grants at both Princeton University and Rutgers University\n* Leverages district-based technical expertise to address national priorities in climate science and planetary exploration",
            "rationale": "Value is based on the specific spending data for NJ-12, citing the $39.5M obligation total and specific research projects at Princeton University provided in the fact sheet.",
